Letting $x=1$, we get the series:

$\begin{align}
\displaystyle\sum\limits_{n=1}^{\infty }\dfrac{(1-3)^n}{n\cdot 2^n}&=\displaystyle\sum\limits_{n=1}^{\infty }\dfrac{(-2)^n}{n\cdot 2^n}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\sum\limits_{n=1}^{\infty }\dfrac{(-1)^n\cdot 2^n}{n\cdot 2^n}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\sum\limits_{n=1}^{\infty }\dfrac{(-1)^n}{n}
\end{align}$

This is the alternating harmonic series, which is known to converge.

